                <p><h2 data-annotate>{{ toc[4].title | allGas | safe}}</h2>. One guide for this could be the F-pattern we discussed earlier. Another high-priority pattern is choosing what content should be <span data-annotate data-ann-color="var(--alert)">"above the fold".</span></p>
                <p>This is a term that dates back to newprint - top headlines were kept in the top half of the page, above where the newspaper would be folded in half horizontally. In the early days of the web, people <em>did not scroll</em> web pages. Like, at all, basically.</p>
            </li>
