    {% endslide %}
    {% slide %}
        <p>This has changed... somewhat.</p>
        <blockquote>In 2010, 80% of the viewing time was spent above the fold. Today, that number is only 57%.<footer><cite><a href="https://www.nngroup.com/articles/scrolling-and-attention/" target="_blank">Norman Nielsen<span class="show-for-sr"> Opens in a new window</span></a>.</cite></footer></blockquote>
        <p>Add to that the fact that responsive design means there is <span data-annotate data-ann-type="underline">no exact spot where the "fold" will be</span> for users. Nonetheless, it's a good rule to follow that <span data-annotate>the higher up the content is, the better the chance users will actually see it.</span></p>
